author: @Veptis
text: "image space is vast". Like a 32x32 image with 256 greyscale pixels has more permutations than particles in the universe through the live of the universe. But the majority of that is all noise. So it's possible to reduce that space to actual useful images. And that space is less than a per cent of that space but still larger than the universe. That's why these models have even more potential   Disco Diffusion has some really interesting walks it can do through latent space, and applying the methods to Stable Diffusion probably produces better results. And it's been more than a year of various Disco Diffusion models. YouTube Channel bycloud made a great overview of the history 3 months ago... Which of course lacks all the advancements of the last 2 months like Stable Diffusion being public.
